<template>
  <div class="view view-terms">
    <page-header>
      <template v-slot:heading>
        Terms of Service
      </template>
    </page-header>
    <div class="container">
      <h3>1. Acceptance</h3>
      <p>The terms stated here represent an agreement between Holmes Web Development (henceforth abbreviated as HWD) and the client.</p>
      <p>Agreement of these terms by both the client and HWD is a prerequisite of the commencement of any work between the client and HWD.</p>
      <p>Failure to adhere to these terms may result in the termination of services provided by HWD.</p>
      <h3>2. Billing</h3>
      <p>Pricing for work supplied by HWD will be quoted, based on the services requested by the client, before commencement of a project. Should the client require additional services at a later stage during the project, additional relevant quotations may be provided.</p>
      <p>A non-refundable of 50% of the original quotation is required before the commencement of work on a project. The remaining 50% must be paid before the deployment of the project.</p>
      <h3>3. Time</h3>
      <p>Time estimates may be provided by HWD, however actual completion times for services may vary from these estimates.</p>
      <h3>4. Client Review</h3>
      <p>In the case of web development, the client will be given the opportunity to review the work and provide feedback and requests at two (2) stages during the development process, namely:
        <ul>
          <li>The design stage, before development begins, whereupon review material will be provided in the form of wireframes and graphic designs.</li>
          <li>The final stage, when the website has been completed, whereupon review material will be provided in the form of the finished website.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h3>5. HWD Portfolio</h3>
      <p>Work supplied by HWD for the client may be added to the portfolio of HWD unless otherwise requested by the client.</p>
      <h3>6. Third-Party Services</h3>
      <p>Certain third-party services may be required for the execution of some services (eg. web hosting, domain name subscriptions, etc.). While HWD may assist in configuring these services for the client, payment for the third-party services will be made from the client directly to the relevant third-party service providers, and the client will be responsible for maintaining working paid subscriptions with the third-party service providers where necessary.</p>
      <h3>7. Attribution</h3>
      <p>By default, the HWD logo with a link to holmeswebdev.com will appear in the footer of any website made by HWD. Removal of the attribution may be purchased for the amount of ZAR 400.</p>
      <h3>8. Liability</h3>
      <p>HWD is excluded from liability in the form of:
        <ul>
          <li>Loss or damage incurred by the client</li>
          <li>Complications pertaining to third-party services</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script>

export default {
  name: 'Terms'
}
</script>



